          'appointment_detail': "Appointment Detail",
          'cat_detail': "Cats are popular as pets, and a healthy cat is a happy and energetic animal. Here's what you need to know about cat health and care:\n\nNutrition: Cats need a high protein diet. Ready-made cat food, specially formulated for cats contain all nutrients to maintain balance. Cats should never be given human food. Also, cats should have access to fresh drinking water.\n\nLiving Space: Cats need a comfortable living space. The living space should be clean and safe, where the cat can move freely Cats should have access to toys, climbing areas, and sleeping areas.\n\nCleanliness: Cats are clean animals and it is important to keep their fur clean. The cat's fur should be brushed regularly. The cat litter box should be cleaned and disinfected daily.\n\ nVeterinary Controls: It is important that cats are subject to regular veterinary control. Care, parasite control and detection of health problems should be visited regularly.\n\nExercise: Cats should exercise regularly. Exercise helps the cat stay healthy and fit. It is recommended that cats play with toys and climb.\n\nSterilization/Sterilization: Sterilization/neutering of cats is important for them to lead a healthy life. These procedures prevent unwanted pregnancies and make the cat more resistant to health problems.\n\nThe tips above will help your cats live healthy and happy lives. However, it is recommended that you consult your veterinarian for more information as cats may have special needs.",
          'cat_life': "12 – 18 year.",
          'dog_detail': "Dogs are known to be loyal and loving pets. Here's what you need to know about the health and care of dogs:\n\nNutrition: The nutrition of dogs is very important for their health. Dogs need protein, carbohydrates, fat and vitamins. Ready-made dog foods, specially formulated for dogs, contain all nutritional elements to provide balance. Dogs should never be given human food. Also, dogs must have access to fresh drinking water.\n\nLiving Space: Dogs need a comfortable living space. The living area should be a clean and safe place where the dog can move freely. Dogs should have access to toys, climbing areas and sleeping areas.\n\nCleanliness: Dogs are clean animals and it is important to keep their coats clean. The coat of the dog should be brushed regularly. Dogs' ears, eyes, and paws should also be cleaned regularly. The dog toilet should be cleaned and disinfected every day.\n\nVeterinary Controls: It is important that dogs are subject to regular veterinary control. The vet should be visited regularly for the dog's vaccination, dental care, parasite control and detection of health problems.\n\nExercise: Dogs should exercise regularly. Exercise helps the dog stay healthy and fit. It is recommended that dogs be taken for walks, play with toys and run.\n\nSterilization/Sterilization: Sterilization/neutering of dogs is important for them to lead a healthy life. These procedures prevent unwanted pregnancies and make the dog more resistant to health problems.\n\nThe above tips will help your dogs live a healthy and happy life. However, it is recommended that you obtain more information by consulting your veterinarian as dogs may have special needs.",
          'fish_life': "5 - 10 year.",
          'fish_detail': "Fish are one of the most popular pets to keep at home. Here's what you need to know about the health and care of fish:\n\nWater Quality: The health and happiness of fish depends on water quality. The fish tank should be filled with clean water with the correct pH level. The water should be tested and cleaned regularly.\n\nNutrition: The nutrition of fish is very important for their health. Fish need protein, carbohydrates, fat and vitamins. Ready-made fish foods are specially formulated for fish and contain all nutrients to provide balance. Fish should never be given human food. In addition, fish must have access to fresh drinking water.\n\nLiving Space: The habitat of fish is important for their health. The fish tank should be a clean and safe place where the fish can move freely. Fish should have swimming areas, vegetation and places to hide. Using a filter in the fish tank helps keep the water clean and the fish healthy.\n\nLighting: The fish tank should be properly lit. Proper lighting helps fish exhibit their natural behavior and helps plants grow.\n\nHeating: Depending on the type of fish, the fish tank should be kept at the right temperature. The fish tank should be equipped with suitable heaters.\n\nMaintenance: The fish tank should be cleaned and maintained regularly. The feathers of the fish should be brushed regularly. The fish tank is a place where fish's toilets should be cleaned regularly.\n\nThe above tips will help your fish live a healthy and happy life. However, as fish may have special needs, it is recommended to consult a veterinarian or an expert fisherman for more information, depending on the fish type and tank size.",
          'rabbit_life': "8 - 14 year.",
          'rabbit_detail': "Rabbits are cute, soft and social animals and can be kept at home. However, rabbits have some special needs to stay healthy and happy. Here's what you need to know about the health and care of rabbits:\n\nLiving Space: Rabbits need a comfortable and safe living space. The habitat of rabbits can vary depending on their size and number. However, it is important that rabbits live in a clean and safe place where they can move freely. Cages or rabbit houses specially designed for rabbits are the most suitable options to meet the needs of rabbits.\n\nNutrition: Proper nutrition is very important for the health of rabbits. Rabbits should be fed diets such as high fiber foods, fresh vegetables and grass dishes. Ready-made rabbit food can also be used, but you should also feed your rabbits vegetables and herbs to provide proper nutrition. Also, rabbits should have access to fresh drinking water.\n\nCleanliness: Rabbits' habitat should be cleaned regularly. The urine and feces of rabbits can be harmful to the health of rabbits. Rabbits' habitat and water bottle should be cleaned at least once a week.\n\nExercise: Rabbits need regular exercise. Adequate movement of rabbits in their habitat helps them maintain their muscle and bone health. To keep your rabbits moving regularly, you can safely run outside by wearing a leash.\n\nVeterinary Checks: Rabbits need regular veterinary checkups. The veterinarian can make the vaccinations necessary for the health and happiness of your rabbits and provide advice to help them live a healthy life.\n\nThe above tips will help your rabbits live a healthy and happy life. However, as rabbits may have special needs, it is recommended to consult with your veterinarian or a specialist rabbit breeder for more information, depending on the breed and age of the rabbit.",
          'bird_life': "8 - 10 year.",
          'bird_detail': "Budgerigars are cute and social pets. They have certain needs to stay healthy and happy. Here's what you need to know about the health and care of budgerigars:\n\nLiving Space: Budgerigars' habitat can vary depending on their size. However, the habitat should be an area where birds can move, fly and exercise freely. The size of the cage should be at least large enough for the birds to spread their wings. The bottom of the cage should be covered with an easy-to-clean material.\n\nNutrition: Budgerigars should be fed a healthy diet. Nutrients such as birdseed, fresh vegetables, fruits, grains and small sources of protein (for example, boiled eggs) should be provided. Also, make sure that fresh water is always cleaned.\n\nCleanliness: Budgerigars' habitat should be cleaned regularly. The cage should be cleaned several times a week, along with all its equipment. This will keep the birds healthy and happy.\n\nExercise: Budgerigars need regular exercise. You can give the birds their exercise by taking them out of the cage and letting them fly around the room. You can also help your budgies exercise by keeping toys in their cages.\n\nVeterinary Checks: Budgerigars need regular veterinary checkups. The veterinarian can make the vaccinations necessary for the health of the birds and provide advice to help the birds live in a healthy way.\n\nThe tips above will help your budgies live a healthy and happy life. However, as budgies may have special needs, it is recommended to consult with your veterinarian or a specialist bird breeder for more information, depending on the type and age of the budgerigar.",
          'turtle_life': "0 - 30 year.",
          'turtle_detail': "House turtles are cute and interesting pets. However, they need to receive the right care so that they can live a healthy and happy life. Here's what you need to know about the health and care of house turtles:\n\nHabitat: Turtles have special needs for their habitat. They are usually kept in aquarium or terrarium-like containers. Their habitat can vary depending on the size and number of turtles. However, the habitat should be an area where turtles can move around, contain a shallow water source, and be heated.\n\nDiet: Turtles stay healthy with proper nutrition. The diet of turtles should include protein sources such as shellfish, vegetables, fruits and insects. It is also important for turtles to take calcium supplements for healthy bones and shells.\n\nWater: Turtles are aquatic animals and they need clean water. The water source should be deep enough for the turtles to swim. Also, the water supply should be cleaned and replaced regularly.\n\nHeating: Turtles are animals that need the right temperature. The habitat should include a heat source such as a heating lamp or heating mat to keep the turtles warm.\n\nVeterinary Checks: Turtles need regular veterinary checkups to stay healthy. The veterinarian can screen your turtles for health and provide advice to help your turtles live a healthy life.\n\nThe tips above will help house turtles live happily and healthily. However, it is recommended to consult your veterinarian or a specialist turtle breeder for more information, depending on the type and age of the turtle.",
          'hamster_life': "2 - 3 year.",
          'hamster_detail': "Hamsters are small and cute pets. A healthy hamster will be happy and active. Here's what you need to know about hamster health and care: \n\nLiving Space: Hamsters should live in a clean cage. The cage should contain basic equipment, such as a wheel, a nest, a water bottle and a feeding bowl, in which the hamster can move freely. Cleaning should be facilitated by laying sawdust or sand under the cage.\n\nNutrition: Hamsters should be fed with a specially prepared hamster food or food such as fresh vegetables, fruits, and dry food. Also, chewing bones can be given to prevent hamsters from growing their teeth.\n\nWater: Hamsters need clean and fresh water. A water bottle should be placed in the cage and the water should be changed regularly.\n\nExercise: Hamsters should get regular exercise. Providing a wheel or playground in the cage helps your hamster exercise.\n\nCleanliness: Hamsters should live in a clean environment. The cage should be cleaned at least once a week. Also, the hamster's fur may need to be brushed, cleaned and trimmed regularly.\n\nHealth Check: Hamsters should be regularly health checked. Your hamster's behavior, appetite and stools should be checked. If you notice any abnormalities, consult your veterinarian.\n\nSocial Communication: Hamsters are social animals. It is better if they coexist with other hamsters. However, same-sex hamsters cannot coexist and may fight. Take time and play regularly to meet your hamster's social needs.\n\nThe above tips will help your hamster live a healthy and happy life. However, it is recommended that you consult your veterinarian for more information as your hamster may have special needs.",
          'horse_life': "25 - 30 year.",
          'horse_detail': "Horses are strong, graceful and special pets. A healthy horse will be energetic and happy. Here's what you need to know about equine health and care:\n\nLiving Space: Horses need a large stable or shelter. The living area should be a clean and safe place where the horse can move freely. In addition, adequate feed and drinking water should be provided.\n\nNutrition: Horse nutrition should include high quality fodder, hay and fresh water. The feeding plan should be based on the age, height, weight and activity level of the horse. Also, horses' teeth should be checked and trimmed regularly.\n\nExercise: Horses should exercise regularly. Exercise helps the horse stay healthy and fit. It is recommended that horses spend most of the day outdoors and engage in activities such as walking, jogging or riding.\n\nCleanliness: It is important for horses to live in a clean environment. The barn or shelter should be cleaned and disinfected regularly. The hair of horses should be brushed and combed regularly. In addition, the nails of the horses should be trimmed regularly.\n\nVeterinary Controls: It is important that the horses are subject to regular veterinary control. The veterinarian should be visited regularly for the horse's vaccination, dental care, parasite control and detection of health problems.\n\nSocial Communication: Horses are social animals and need to live together with other horses. Suitable companions must be found for the horses to live with. Horses are also recommended to socialize and train with humans.\n\nThe above tips will help your horses live a healthy and happy life. However, as horses may have special needs, it is recommended to consult your veterinarian for more information.",
